## 🚀 How to Run

```powershell
# Start backend (port 5000)
node server.js

# Start frontend (port 8080)
npm run dev
```

> Both are currently running. Frontend: http://localhost:8080 | Backend: http://localhost:5000

---

## ⚠️ Known Gaps (Future Work)

| Gap | Notes |
|-----|-------|
| No frontend route guards | Unauthenticated users can access `/dashboard/*` routes by URL |
| Passwords stored as plaintext | No bcrypt hashing — **not production-safe** |
| Chart data (weekly revenue, monthly bookings) uses dummy numbers | No per-day aggregation endpoint exists yet |
| No email verification | Users can sign up with any email |
| No pagination | Tables load all records (fine for demo scale) |
| Super admin `tenant_id` = 1 (hardcoded seed) | Required by FK constraint — works but is a design quirk |
